Disaster Declaration Asked
   For 5 California Counties
"I am requesting the federal declaration to ease the
burden on local government, to provide additional assistance
to area residents and businesses," Gov. Wilson said. The
counties affected are Los Angeles, Ventura, Orange, San
Bernardino and Kern.
   The state Office of Emergency Services estimated the
storms caused more than $94 million of damage to public
property. In addition, Gov. Wilson estimated that uninsured
businesses suffered $8.5 million of damage.